  "title": "Media Specialist (Search & Social)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>CARAT MEDIA SERVICES SINGAPORE PTE LTD</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>dentsu is seeking a motivated and detail-oriented Media  Specialist to join our Media team for a 6-months programme. This role supports Search and Social media initiatives and provides hands-on exposure to digital marketing campaigns within a leading integrated communications network.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Support the planning, execution, and optimization of Search and Social media campaigns to drive campaign effectiveness and client objectives</li><li>Assist in managing day-to-day campaign activities across platforms such as Google Ads, Meta, TikTok, and other social channels to ensure seamless delivery</li><li>Monitor campaign performance data and contribute to reporting and analysis to inform strategic adjustments</li><li>Conduct market, audience, and competitor research to provide actionable insights that enhance media strategies</li><li>Prepare media reports, presentations, and internal documentation to communicate campaign progress and results clearly</li><li>Collaborate with internal teams to ensure accurate and timely campaign delivery aligned with client expectations</li><li>Demonstrate proactive learning and teamwork to contribute effectively within a dynamic media environment</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Basic knowledge of digital marketing with a focus on Search and Social media platforms including Meta, TikTok, and YouTube</li><li>Familiarity with digital advertising platforms such as Google Ads and Meta Ads Manager</li><li>Strong analytical skills applied to campaign data interpretation and optimization</li><li>Effective written and verbal communication skills for clear reporting and collaboration</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint, and Google Workspace to support campaign documentation and presentations</li><li>Ability to commit full-time to a 6-month programme</li></ul>",
